# CSS Layers

| File | Contains | Must NOT contain |
|---|---|---|
| `src/shutters-core.css` | Grid animation, opacity, icon rotation, header flex, cursor | Colors, borders, padding, fonts |
| `src/shutters-theme.css` | Colors, borders, padding, typography, `:focus-visible` | Grid mechanics duplication |
| `demo/shutters-demo.css` | Demo page layout only | Library styles |

## Animation pattern (do not change approach)

```css
.shutters-content { display: grid; grid-template-rows: 0fr; opacity: 0; }
.opened .shutters-content { grid-template-rows: 1fr; opacity: 1; }
.shutters-body { min-height: 0; overflow: hidden; }
```

## Theme custom properties

`--shutters-bg-color`, `--shutters-border-color`, `--shutters-focus-color`, `--shutters-hover-bg`, `--shutters-text-color`

JS also sets `--shutters-animation-duration` and `--shutters-animation-easing` inline on containers.

## After CSS changes

- [ ] Sync matching file to `demo/` if it's a library CSS file
- [ ] `npm run build` and visually check demo
- [ ] `npm run agent:sync`
